item.title: My parents put a system pass on my comp how do i find it out?
item.dc:creator: @Drunk_On_Java Drunk On Java
item.description:
@Drunk_On_Java wrote:

[quote=“moparisthebest, post:28, topic:16252”][quote author=Drunk On Java link=topic=24294.msg273551#msg273551 date=1159248364]
Haxor, that is stored in the bios, go hack the cmos. Search the google for cmos and bios.
[/quote]

That is a complete lie, windows stores nothing in the bios, it is 100% impossible, Drunk on Java, reread the rule about this being an informative, not a misinformative community.

With windows xp I did this a long time ago in high school, (that was before SP1), there is a hidden file someplace that you don’t have access to from windows, however if you boot into linux (try Damn Small Linux (DSL) you can view the file and find the passwords. Google would probably be your best help on this :)[/quote]
No, mopar what I was talking about (thnking what he is talking about) is like on dell computers you can set a startup password that is stored in the bios. Go google it. It’s true as I have done this at least 4 or 5 times on dell computers, it may have the option to do so in other brands as well.
